docs.snippet: An erratic movement of the Australian pound spotlighted the trading in the foreign exchanges last week. Liquidation of speculative positions built up in anticipation of an upward revaluation of the pound which did not materialize produced heavy...
docs.lead_paragraph: An erratic movement of the Australian pound spotlighted the trading in the foreign exchanges last week. Liquidation of speculative positions built up in anticipation of an upward revaluation of the pound which did not materialize produced heavy offerings and depressed the rate from $2.22 on Monday, to $2.18 on Thursday.
